#### Rune of the Fallen Crusader

#### Rune of Spellbreaking
**Prerequisite: 14th level**

In addition, you can expend a rune of power to end one spell on yourself as an action. 

### Lichborne
*8th-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You can't be charmed or frightened, and magic can't put you to sleep.

### Death's Advance
*9th-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

Your movement is unaffected by difficult terrain, and spells and other magical effects cannot reduce your speed.

### Empowered rune weapon
*11th-level death knight feature*

<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

The runes inscribed in your weapon begin to resonate, building off of each other's power. Whenever you would gain a rune of power, you instead gain two runes.

Additionally as an action, you can draw deep upon your rune weapon to recharge your abilities, regaining all expended runes of power. Once you use this ability, you cannot do so again until you finish a long rest.

### Will of the Necropolis
*13th-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

If you drop to 0 hit points and don't die outright, you can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. If you succeed, you drop to 1 hit point instead.

Each time you use this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. When you finish a short or long rest, the DC resets to 10.

### UNKNOWN-15
*15th-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>



### Hungering rune weapon
*17th-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

Whenever you would gain a rune of power, you instead gain three runes.

### Deathlord
*20th-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

**[Unknown. Related to rune weapons. Limited immortality?]**

